body_text.text:
In this study, the concept of the SVE3∗ was applied to calculate the UV dose of the exhaled air from a patient. The mouth of a patient was treated as another supply opening, like those of the air conditioning or ventilation systems, to find the contribution ratio of the exhaled air from the patient (Fig. 2
). In addition, it was assumed that the mouth constantly exhales only, like other supply openings, to calculate the contribution ratio, which can be obtained in steady state flow and diffusion fields (Fig. 3
).
